<html><head><meta http-equiv="Content-Type" content="text/html; charset=utf-8" /><meta http-equiv="Content-Style-Type" content="text/css" /><meta name="generator" content="Aspose.Words for .NET 13.4.0.0" /><title>Written evidence submitted to IDSC Inquiry on Disability and Development by Mark Harrison and Bill Albert, researchers and members of Equal Lives, the largest disabled persons organization (DPO) in the UK</title></head><body><div><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 15pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:14pt; font-weight:bold; letter-spacing:0.25pt">Written evidence submitted to </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:14pt; font-weight:bold; letter-spacing:0.25pt">IDSC Inquiry on Disability and Development </span><span style="color:#17365d; font-family:Arial; font-size:14pt; font-weight:bold; letter-spacing:0.25pt">by Mark Harrison and Bill Albert, </span><span style="color:#17365d; font-family:Arial; font-size:14pt; font-weight:bold; letter-spacing:0.25pt">as individual </span><span style="color:#17365d; font-family:Arial; font-size:14pt; font-weight:bold; letter-spacing:0.25pt">researchers and </span><span style="color:#17365d; font-family:Arial; font-size:14pt; font-weight:bold; letter-spacing:0.25pt">as </span><span style="color:#17365d; font-family:Arial; font-size:14pt; font-weight:bold; letter-spacing:0.25pt">members of Equal Lives</span><span style="color:#17365d; font-family:Arial; font-size:14pt; font-weight:bold; letter-spacing:0.25pt"> </span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:14pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Arial; font-size:14pt; font-weight:bold; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 16.68pt; padding-left:1.32pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:14pt; font-weight:bold">Executive Summary</span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 18pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:14pt; font-weight:bold">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 39.6pt; text-indent:-21.6pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:14pt">1.1.</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:14pt">Evidence is</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:14pt"> being submitted by disabled researchers with considerable experience of working with DFID on disability and development.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 39.6pt; text-indent:-21.6pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:14pt">1.2.</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:14pt">DFID has made many positive statements and has contracted out various useful interventions on disability in development cooperation.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 39.6pt; text-indent:-21.6pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:14pt">1.3.</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:14pt">T</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:14pt">here are substantial structural barriers on the international level which make inclusion of disability problematic for DFID.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 39.6pt; text-indent:-21.6pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:14pt">1.4.</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:14pt">The contracting out of work on disability, making it essentially a special interest topic, has made it difficult to adopt a </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:14pt">twin-track approach and mainstream disability within DFID.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 39.6pt; text-indent:-21.6pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:14pt">1.5.</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:14pt">Substantive reforms within the Department are needed in order to imbed disability effectively in policy and practice.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:14pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="2" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Arial; font-size:14pt; font-weight:bold; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 16.68pt; padding-left:1.32pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:14pt; font-weight:bold">Those submitting evidence are:</span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:14pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 39.6pt; text-indent:-21.6pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:14pt">2.1.</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:14pt">Disabled researchers active in the UK disabili</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:14pt">ty movement who worked at the University of East Anglia</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:14pt">’</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:14pt">s Department of International Development on a number of disability and development projects for DFID between 2002 and 2006/07. </span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 39.6pt; text-indent:-21.6pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:14pt">2.2.</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:14pt">Albert was part of a team who assessed the first Disability Knowledge a</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:14pt">nd Research (</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:14pt">KaR</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:14pt">) </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:14pt">Programme</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:14pt"> in 2003/04. Harrison became director of second Disability </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:14pt">KaR</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:14pt"> and Albert was research director. </span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 39.6pt; text-indent:-21.6pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:14pt">2.3.</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:14pt">The overarching theme of the second </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:14pt">KaR</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:14pt"> was to study disability mainstreaming in development practice at DFID and internationally. </span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 39.6pt; text-indent:-21.6pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:14pt">2.4.</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:14pt">To do this, they set up a unique South-North disabled-person led research </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:14pt">programme</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:14pt">. The widely disseminated </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:14pt">findings </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:14pt">were brought together in a monograph (</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:14pt; font-weight:bold">In or Out of </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:14pt; font-weight:bold">The</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:14pt; font-weight:bold"> Mainstream? Lessons from Research on Disability and Development Cooperation</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:14pt; font-weight:bold">) </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:14pt">funde</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:14pt">d by DFID and published by the University of Leeds.</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:14pt"> </span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 39.6pt; text-indent:-21.6pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:14pt">2.5.</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:14pt">Subsequently, both Albert and Harrison took part in a British Council of Disabled People</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:14pt">’</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:14pt">s consultation for DFID focused on disability-related issues, including identifying barriers to mainstreaming. </span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 39.6pt; text-indent:-21.6pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:14pt">2.6.</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:14pt">Th</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:14pt">ey also helped write DFID</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:14pt">’</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:14pt">s 2007 How To Note, </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:14pt; font-weight:bold">Working on Disability in Country </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:14pt; font-weight:bold">Programmes</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:14pt">, carried out disability awareness training for staff in London and East </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:14pt">Kilbride</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:14pt">,  a</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:14pt">s</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:14pt"> well as </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:14pt">devising a similar training </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:14pt">programme</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:14pt"> for country offices. </span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 39.6pt; text-indent:-21.6pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:14pt">2.7.</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:14pt">Both also </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:14pt">have extensive experience working closely with Disabled People</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:14pt">’</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:14pt">s </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:14pt">Organisations</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:14pt"> (DPOs) in the Commonwealth, Russia, Bulgaria and Southern Africa.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 39.6pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:14pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="3" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Arial; font-size:14pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 16.68pt; padding-left:1.32pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:14pt">Although the work on the Disability </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:14pt">KaR</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:14pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:14pt">programme</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:14pt"> was completed about six years ago, a review of DFID</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:14pt">’</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:14pt">s curren</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:14pt">t disability profile and discussion with colleagues suggests that little has changed, the main points raised at the time are still broadly valid and disability remains outside the mainstream policy and practice at DFID.  </span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:14pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="4" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Arial; font-size:14pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 16.68pt; padding-left:1.32pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:14pt; font-weight:bold">DFID</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:14pt; font-weight:bold">’</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:14pt; font-weight:bold">s positive disability interv</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:14pt; font-weight:bold">entions</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:14pt">.</span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:14pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 39.6pt; text-indent:-21.6pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:14pt">4.1.</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:14pt">DFID funds various NGOs that carry out valuable project work in the South.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 86.4pt; text-indent:-32.4pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:14pt">4.1.1.1.</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:14pt">Of these, perhaps Action on Disability and Development stands out as the most prominent.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 39.6pt; text-indent:-21.6pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:14pt">4.2.</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:14pt">DFID provides about </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:14pt">£</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:14pt">1m a year for the </span><span style="font-family:Helvetica; font-size:14pt">Disability Rights Fund</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:14pt"> that offers project funding directly to Southern DPOs.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 39.6pt; text-indent:-21.6pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:14pt">4.3.</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:14pt">DFID funds the Leonard Cheshire Disability and Inclusive Development Centre at University College London.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 39.6pt; text-indent:-21.6pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:14pt">4.4.</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:14pt">Disability has been strongly promoted with respect to DFID staff (Disability Core Script 2013)</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:14pt">.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 39.6pt; text-indent:-21.6pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:14pt">4.5.</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:14pt">Following one of the recommendations of the Disability </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:14pt">KaR</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:14pt">, a major disability research </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:14pt">programme</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:14pt"> was developed with SAFOD (Southern Africa </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:14pt">Organisation</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:14pt"> of the Disabled). </span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 39.6pt; text-indent:-21.6pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:14pt">4.6.</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:14pt">There are individuals within </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:14pt">DFiD</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:14pt">, including the Permanent Secretary, Mark </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:14pt">Lowcock</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:14pt">, who have championed disability issues.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 39.6pt; text-indent:-21.6pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:14pt">4.7.</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:14pt">DFID has had a lead role in promoting disability in international forums, but positive statements have, by in large, have not translated into effective practice within DFID itself.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:14pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:14pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="5" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Arial; font-size:14pt; font-weight:bold; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 16.68pt; padding-left:1.32pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:14pt; font-weight:bold">Barriers to mainstreaming disabi</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:14pt; font-weight:bold">lity at DFID</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:14pt; font-weight:bold"> </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:14pt; font-weight:bold">- the international level</span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:14pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 39.6pt; text-indent:-21.6pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:14pt">5.1.</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:14pt">The absence of disability in the MDG</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:14pt">’</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:14pt">s, a touchstone for policy and practice at DFID, as well as other national development agencies, has been a major barrier to having disability seen as a key issue.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 39.6pt; text-indent:-21.6pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:14pt">5.2.</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:14pt">Despite the </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:14pt">recommendations from UN</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:14pt">’</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:14pt">s High Level Meeting on Disability &amp; Development in September 2013 and the UK</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:14pt">’</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:14pt">s support for these recommendations, so far disability has found no substantive mention in subsequent meetings of the Open Working Group on Sustainable De</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:14pt">velopment Goals. </span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 39.6pt; text-indent:-21.6pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:14pt">5.3.</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:14pt">The failure to get disability included within Multilateral Aid Documents has proved a major break on disability inclusion.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 39.6pt; text-indent:-21.6pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:14pt">5.4.</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:14pt">The continued move away from conditionality in development </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:14pt">aid  has</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:14pt"> made it difficult to promote disability as a cr</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:14pt">oss-cutting issue. </span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 39.6pt; text-indent:-21.6pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:14pt">5.5.</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:14pt">Lack of reliable data on the incidence of disability in the South is often used as a reason for not mainstreaming.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 39.6pt; text-indent:-21.6pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:14pt">5.6.</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:14pt">Although disability is mentioned in many countries PRSPs, the narrow focus, in line with priorities of the World Bank and</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:14pt"> IMF, on economic indicators has resulted in scant progress for disabled people in the South.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 39.6pt; text-indent:-21.6pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:14pt">5.7.</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:14pt">Many countries have made strong statements on disability and development and/or have official disability policies, but most of these have not be implemented and r</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:14pt">emain only as good intensions trapped on paper.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:14pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="6" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Arial; font-size:14pt; font-weight:bold; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 16.68pt; padding-left:1.32pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:14pt; font-weight:bold">Barriers to mainstreaming disability at DFID</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:14pt; font-weight:bold"> </span><span style="font-family:'Arial Unicode MS'; font-size:14pt; font-weight:bold">–</span><span style="font-family:'Arial Unicode MS'; font-size:14pt; font-weight:bold"> </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:14pt; font-weight:bold">departmental level</span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:14pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 39.6pt; text-indent:-21.6pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:14pt">6.1.</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:14pt">The contracting out of disability interventions to NGOs directed by non-disabled people has been problematic.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 111.6pt; text-indent:-39.6pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:14pt">6.1.1.1.1.</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:14pt">In our research, many disabled</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:14pt"> people and DPOs in the South saw NGOs as part of the problem, rather than part of the solution.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 162pt; text-indent:-54pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:14pt">6.1.1.1.1.1.1.</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:14pt">This stemmed from the massive inequality in their relationship and the strong tendency for NGOs to impose Northern priorities in working with DPOs in the </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:14pt">South.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 162pt; text-indent:-54pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:14pt">6.1.1.1.1.1.2.</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:14pt">One of the important conclusions of the </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:14pt">KaR</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:14pt"> research was: </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:14pt">‘The Northern NGOs tend to use the southern DPOs because at the end, they benefit more from these proposals.’ At the same time, even with the best intentions on behalf of NGOs, new forms of d</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:14pt">ependency for disabled people and their </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:14pt">organisations</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:14pt"> are being created.</span><span style="font-family:FranklinGothic; font-size:12pt"> </span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 162pt; text-indent:-54pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:14pt">6.1.1.1.1.1.3.</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:14pt">Another, and closely related problem is that in most cases NGOS are managed and staffed in country by non-disabled people who, however good intentioned, do not share the life experie</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:14pt">nce of disability.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 162pt; text-indent:-54pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:14pt">6.1.1.1.1.1.4.</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:14pt">The opposite is true in most Scandinavian countries, where domestic DPOs, with first-hand experience of disability, are supported by their governments to undertake disability work in the South.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 187.2pt; text-indent:-61.2pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:14pt">6.1.1.1.1.1.4.1.</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:14pt">Although not problem free, this approach </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:14pt">has resulted on the whole in more </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:14pt">successful and sustained outcomes for disabled people in the South.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 162pt; text-indent:-54pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:14pt">6.1.1.1.1.1.5.</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:14pt">Because of Southern DPOs financial dependency on Northern NGOs, these issues are rarely brought up.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 111.6pt; text-indent:-39.6pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:14pt">6.1.1.1.2.</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:14pt">An excellent example of an alternative working model i</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:14pt">s offered by DFID’s direct funding of a five-year research project with SAFOD – Southern Africa </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:14pt">Organisation</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:14pt"> of the Disabled.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 136.8pt; text-indent:-46.8pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:14pt">6.1.1.1.2.1.</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:14pt">This project has seen the training of disabled researchers and much of the direction and administration carried out by disabled pe</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:14pt">ople from countries in Southern Africa.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 136.8pt; text-indent:-46.8pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:14pt">6.1.1.1.2.2.</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:14pt">This has meant much greater self-direction, self empowerment and sustainability for disabled people. </span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 39.6pt; text-indent:-21.6pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:14pt">6.2.</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:14pt">Contracting out has essentially assigned disability to the category of a </span><span style="font-family:'Arial Unicode MS'; font-size:14pt">‘</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:14pt">special interest concern</span><span style="font-family:'Arial Unicode MS'; font-size:14pt">’</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:14pt">, thereby reinf</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:14pt">orcing the widespread assumption that disability and disabled people are outside the mainstream.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 61.2pt; text-indent:-25.2pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:14pt">6.2.1.</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'"> </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:14pt">Separate disability projects should be welcomed, but not if they result, as they have,</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:14pt"> in a </span><span style="font-family:'Arial Unicode MS'; font-size:14pt">‘</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:14pt">one-track</span><span style="font-family:'Arial Unicode MS'; font-size:14pt">’</span><span style="font-family:'Arial Unicode MS'; font-size:14pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:14pt">approach, rather than a twin-track approach to disabili</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:14pt">ty. </span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 39.6pt; text-indent:-21.6pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:14pt">6.3.</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:14pt">There is no official disability policy or disability strategy at DFID.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 39.6pt; text-indent:-21.6pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:14pt">6.4.</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:14pt">There is no lead person on disability in the Department.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 39.6pt; text-indent:-21.6pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:14pt">6.5.</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:14pt">Disability and development issues are not widely understood in DFID.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 39.6pt; text-indent:-21.6pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:14pt">6.6.</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:14pt">DFID</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:14pt">’</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:14pt">s business plan 2012-2015 contains no mention of </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:14pt">disability</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 39.6pt; text-indent:-21.6pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:14pt">6.7.</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:14pt">Disability is not identified as an official cross-cutting issue.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 39.6pt; text-indent:-21.6pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:14pt">6.8.</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:14pt">There is little understanding of the UN Convention on the Rights of People with Disabilities, particularly </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:14pt">Article </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:14pt">32</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:14pt">, that</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:14pt"> mentions the need to include national DPOs of donor coun</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:14pt">tries in disability and development interventions.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:14pt; font-weight:bold">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="7" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Arial; font-size:14pt; font-weight:bold; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 16.68pt; padding-left:1.32pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:14pt; font-weight:bold">Recommendations for mainstreaming disability within DFID</span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:14pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 36pt 0pt 0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:14pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 36pt 0pt 39.6pt; text-indent:-21.6pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:14pt">7.1.</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:14pt">Co-produce policies and working practices with DPOs in the UK and the South</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 36pt 0pt 0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:14pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 36pt 0pt 39.6pt; text-indent:-21.6pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:14pt">7.2.</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:14pt">Work more assiduously to ensure disability is included in the new </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:14pt">SDGs</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 36pt; text-indent:-18pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:14pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 36pt 0pt 39.6pt; text-indent:-21.6pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:14pt">7.3.</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:14pt">Devise a clear official policy and mandate for disability</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 36pt 0pt 0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:14pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 36pt 0pt 39.6pt; text-indent:-21.6pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:14pt">7.4.</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:14pt">Adopt disability as an official cross-cutting issue similar to gender</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 36pt 0pt 0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:14pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 36pt 0pt 39.6pt; text-indent:-21.6pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:14pt">7.5.</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:14pt">Develop an implementation strategy with accountable, time-bound goals both in terms of employment and </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:14pt">programme</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:14pt"> work </span></p><p style="margin:0pt 36pt 0pt 0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:14pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 36pt 0pt 39.6pt; text-indent:-21.6pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:14pt">7.6.</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:14pt">C</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:14pt">onsider how disability policy, mandate and strategy can be most effectively communicated throughout DFID</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 36pt 0pt 0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:14pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 36pt 0pt 39.6pt; text-indent:-21.6pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:14pt">7.7.</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:14pt">Establish a sub-group with specific responsibility for disability in the appropriate section within DFID</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 36pt 0pt 0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:14pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 36pt 0pt 39.6pt; text-indent:-21.6pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:14pt">7.8.</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:14pt">Appoint a disability officer/advisor to cham</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:14pt">pion disability issues</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 36pt 0pt 0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:14pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 36pt 0pt 39.6pt; text-indent:-21.6pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:14pt">7.9.</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:14pt">Address training issues on disability and development</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 36pt 0pt 0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:14pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 36pt 0pt 39.6pt; text-indent:-21.6pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:14pt">7.10.</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:14pt">Devise appropriate monitoring and evaluation systems together with DPOs</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 36pt 0pt 0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:14pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 36pt 0pt 39.6pt; text-indent:-21.6pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:14pt">7.11.</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:14pt">Collect disability-disaggregated data and develop a disability-based equivalent to gender analysis</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 36pt 0pt 0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:14pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 36pt 0pt 39.6pt; text-indent:-21.6pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:14pt">7.12.</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:14pt">Exte</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:14pt">nd consultation on a permanent basis with DPOs in both the North and South</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 36pt 0pt 0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:14pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 36pt 0pt 39.6pt; text-indent:-21.6pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:14pt">7.13.</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:14pt">Develop methods and practices to ensure that disability is taken on board as a cross-cutting human rights issue in multilateral aid instruments</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 36pt 0pt 0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:14pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 36pt 0pt 39.6pt; text-indent:-21.6pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:14pt">7.14.</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:14pt">Demonstrate a practical commitment </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:14pt">to mainstreaming disability by earmarking appropriate levels of funding</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 36pt 0pt 0pt; text-indent:4pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:14pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 36pt 0pt 0pt; text-indent:4pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:14pt; font-weight:bold">Note on sources for Disability </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:14pt; font-weight:bold">KaR</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 36pt 0pt 0pt; text-indent:4pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:14pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 36pt 0pt 0pt; text-indent:4pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:14pt">Although the original website for the project has been taken down, most of the research findings can still be found at: </span><a href="https://web.archive.org/web/20060220105554/http://www.disabilitykar.net/"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:14pt; text-decoration:unde